                <h2 id="post-1124">
                    <a href="http://joyridelabs.de/blog/?p=1124" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Windows bugfix: libstdc++-6.dll was not found">
                        <span class="blogHeadline">Windows bugfix: libstdc++-6.dll was not found</span>
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <small>Thursday, September 22nd, 2011</small>

                <div>
                    <div class="en"><p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://joyridelabs.de/blog//wp-content/uploads/2011/09/libstdcppmissing1.png" alt="core.exe: libstdc++-6.dll not found" title="core.exe: libstdc++-6.dll not found" width="443" height="119" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1132" /></p>

<p>If you see above error message when trying to run Nikki and the Robots, please download libstdc++-6.dll <a href="http://www.box.net/shared/lm6ctv1ejny4q43fj4od">here</a> and unzip it to the <strong>nikki\</strong> directory or alternatively <a href="http://joyridelabs.de/game/download/">download</a> the game again - the problem has been fixed in the latest release for Windows.</p>

<p>PS: the updater won't restart the game on Windows! (Also fixed in the new release.)</p></div>
                </div>
